The paper deals with image labeling problems such as segmentation and image reconstruction, which are typically studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper proposes a framework for discovering compact representations of higher order priors, which involves optimization and inference techniques that are commonly studied in optimization (cs.GR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
